  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I delete snapchat conversation without using clear conversations?",
  "response": "If you want to delete specific Snapchat conversations without using the **\"Clear Conversations\"** feature (which removes all your chats at once), you can delete individual conversations or messages. Here's how to do it:\n\n### **Delete an Entire Conversation**\n\n1. **Open Snapchat** and log in to your account.\n\n2. **Navigate to the Chat Screen**:\n   - Swipe right from the Camera screen to access the **Chat** screen where all your conversations are listed.\n\n3. **Find the Conversation** you want to delete:\n   - Scroll through your chat list to locate the specific conversation.\n\n4. **Delete the Conversation**:\n   - **iOS Devices**:\n     - Press and hold (long-press) on the conversation you wish to delete.\n     - A menu will appear; select **\"Delete\"**.\n   - **Android Devices**:\n     - Press and hold (long-press) on the conversation.\n     - Tap on the **trash can icon** or **\"Delete Conversation\"** option that appears.\n\n5. **Confirm Deletion**:\n   - A prompt will appear asking you to confirm. Tap **\"Delete\"** to remove the conversation from your chat list.\n\n   > **Note:** This action only removes the conversation from your device. The other person in the chat will still have access to the conversation unless they also delete it on their end.\n\n### **Delete Individual Messages Within a Conversation**\n\nIf you prefer to delete specific messages within a conversation rather than the entire chat, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Snapchat** and go to the **Chat** screen by swiping right.\n\n2. **Select the Conversation** containing the message you want to delete.\n\n3. **Find the Specific Message**:\n   - Scroll through the chat to locate the message you wish to remove.\n\n4. **Delete the Message**:\n   - **iOS Devices**:\n     - Press and hold the specific message.\n     - Tap **\"Delete\"** from the options that appear.\n   - **Android Devices**:\n     - Press and hold the message until a menu appears.\n     - Select **\"Delete\"**.\n\n5. **Confirm Deletion**:\n   - A confirmation prompt will appear. Tap **\"Delete\"** to remove the message.\n\n   > **Important:** Deleting a message only removes it from your view. The recipient will still see the message unless they also delete it.\n\n### **Additional Tips**\n\n- **Remember** that deleting conversations or messages is **per device**. If you use Snapchat on multiple devices, you'll need to delete the conversation on each device separately.\n  \n- **Privacy Consideration**: While deleting conversations can help manage your chat list and maintain privacy on your device, Snapchat messages are generally deleted from their servers after they're viewed or after a set period. However, users can take screenshots or use other methods to save messages before deletion.\n\nBy following these steps, you can manage and delete specific conversations or messages on Snapchat without clearing all your chats at once.",
